x4freetext: Experiment performed at coupled
cyclotron facility at the National Superconducting
Cyclotron Laboratory, East Lansing
Reaction products were analyzed by
combination of A1800 fragment separator and S800 beam
analyzing spectrometer. Momentum analyzed particles
were detected in focal plane of the S800 beam line
At the end of the S800 analysis beam
line, the particles of interest were stopped in a
telescope of eight silicon PIN diodes (50 x 50 mm2
each) with a total thickness of 8.0 mm. A 50-mm-thick
plastic scintillator positioned behind the Si
telescope served as a veto detector against reactions
in the Si telescope and provided a measurement of the
residual energy of lighter ions that were not stopped
in the Si telescope.
A position-sensitive parallel plate avalanche
counter was located in front of the Si telescope to
determine position of charged particles.
